it's v simple, what raster do you want? a raster is 1) extent 2) dimension 3) projection

ie 6 numbers and a string, specify those, give the warper your filename, DONE

no need for complicated formats or preparation, any plot (ready for an image) provides xlim,ylim,dim 

#rstats

#rstats have a big raster problem?need ways to "speed up" your task?  consider making it (the raster) smaller - crop it, or resample it (to lower resolution), or *both* 

R's been a mess on this basic idea in the past, but getting better - hmu if this sounds useful

raster:: aggregate was always slow

stars/terra offer better but:  *my interest* is crop AND subset at read time,  definitely the most efficient... 

but even better: *the warper* (the gdal raster reproject engine) also acts *as reader*

all the things *in one first step* #rstats
